content.description: Sit start with a left hand sidepull and a right hand gaston-ball. From there, pull up to a right hand edge, follow to a left hand sidepull crimp, make a big move to a right hand sidepull, follow to left hand edge, gain the jug shelf above, follow to the lip, and mantel on top.
content.protection: At least a pair of pads. It has a good landing, but there is a rock that makes it uneven.
content.location: It climbs the west face of Energizer.

content.description: Sit start with hands matched on the undercling. From there, pull to a pair of great holds, bring the feet up, use a pair of two-finger pockets to reach an edge at the lip, and mantel on top.
content.protection: A pad will work. The landing is great.
content.location: It climbs the northwest corner of Energizer.

content.description: Sit start with a low left hand sidepull and a good right hand sidepull. From there, stand up to a right hand sidepull on the quasi-arete, bump the left hand up through your choice of sidepull to reach an edge, bump the right hand up to a teardrop pocket, follow to the lip, and mantel on top.
content.protection: A pair of pads. The landing is great, but there is a rock directly left of where the problem climbs.
content.location: It climbs the northwest corner of Energizer.
